# Memory Garden — Cursor Rules

## Commands
```bash
npm run dev       # Start Vite dev server (port 5173)
npm run build     # Type-check + Vite build
npm run lint      # ESLint
npm run test      # Vitest run
npm run preview   # Preview production build
npm run kill      # Kill process on port 5000
```
Always run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps` if node_modules is missing.

## Platform
This is a **GitHub Spark** app. Key SDK APIs:
- `useKV(key, default)` — persistent KV storage per user (replaces a database)
- `window.spark.user()` — GitHub-authenticated user info
- `window.spark.llm(prompt, model)` — LLM calls (`gpt-4o-mini` for classification, `gpt-4o` for generation)

No backend, no external API. All memory data (including photos as Base64 Data URLs) lives in the KV store.

## Architecture
- `App.tsx` — owns all state; reads/writes `memories` and `preferences` via `useKV`
- `GardenCanvas.tsx` — infinite pannable/zoomable HTML5 Canvas (primary view)
- `PlantMemoryModal.tsx` — creation flow (photo upload → Base64, text, date, optional location + audio)
- `MemoryCard.tsx` — detail/tending view; "Water & Reflect" adds a reflection; "Ask Garden AI" calls LLM
- `MemoryClusters.tsx` — AI-suggested groupings (secondary view)
- `Onboarding.tsx` — 4-step first-run tour
- `src/lib/garden-helpers.ts` — growth logic, OKLCH color maps, seasonal gradients, AI call wrappers
- `src/lib/types.ts` — core data model

## Core Data Model
- `Memory` — `id`, `photoUrl` (Base64), `text`, `emotionalTone`, `plantStage`, `position` (x/y), `visitCount`, `reflections[]`
- `PlantStage`: `seed → sprout → bud → bloom → mature → evergreen`
- `EmotionalTone`: `happy | reflective | bittersweet | peaceful | nostalgic`

## Conventions
- **Colors**: OKLCH values only (see `garden-helpers.ts` and `src/styles/theme.css`). No hex/RGB.
- **Animations**: Framer Motion with spring physics. No abrupt transitions.
- **UI components**: Radix UI primitives from `src/components/ui/`. No raw HTML equivalents.
- **Icons**: Phosphor Icons (`@phosphor-icons/react`) for app icons; Lucide for shadcn/ui.
- **Metaphor**: Everything should feel organic and peaceful — garden metaphor is load-bearing.
- **AI fallbacks**: All `window.spark.llm` calls must have `try/catch` with graceful fallback.
- **Photos**: Base64 Data URLs stored inside KV memory objects — no external file storage.
- **Comments**: Default to no comments. Only explain non-obvious WHY, not what.
- **State**: No external state library. Pass handlers down from `App.tsx`.
